## design SDK pro-rata consumption

The gm site (site/theme.mjs) consumes the anentrypoint-design SDK pro-rata, never overriding it. theme.mjs loads the SDK at runtime via unpkg anentrypoint-design@latest (SDK_CSS/SDK_JS, runtime-loaded so @latest auto-picks-up upstream; site/package.json ^0.0.221 is build-time only, not the shipped runtime ref). The local theme.mjs <style> block carries ONLY render-mode plumbing -- the flatspace html-class toggles (article-flow frees the SDK fixed-viewport app-shell so a long article flows+document scrolls; landing-capped caps prose-landing measure; the 640px crumb chip-hide) -- plus site article-layout rhythm (.app-main heading margins, .ds-lede, .work-detail-chips) that is not a reusable SDK component. Every themed VISUAL component (TOC sidebar grid #ds-article-host.has-toc, .cli block, .panel .row, .ds-prose card/tag/gm-callout, ds-prose typography) lives in the SDK (gm-prose.css, token-only) NOT in theme.mjs; a new local CSS rule styling a visual component is a deviation -- make the change in the SDK repo (../anentrypoint-design, GitHub AnEntrypoint/design, npm anentrypoint-design) and publish, the site picks it up via @latest. SDK component sheets are lint-gated literal-free (lint-tokens.mjs COMPONENT_SHEETS, every color a var(--token), no raw hex/rgb/hsl/oklch); SDK build (scripts/build.mjs) postcss-prefixes all selectors with the .ds-247420 scope and gzip+base64-embeds css into the js bundle which self-injects a runtime <style>. Pushing to AnEntrypoint/design main triggers its publish.yml (npm version patch, rebuild, npm publish with NPM_TOKEN) -- the push is the publish trigger, local npm publish is unauthenticated. Witness pro-rata by removing a local override and confirming the component still renders from the SDK via the browser verb page.evaluate (clean console, only unpkg css/js in network).